The 3D Smith Chart application is developed using the Java programming language and the following libraries and development environment are used:
3D rendering: OpenGL through the Java Binding for the Open GL API (JOGL2) library;
Mathematical operations and complex data representation: The Apache Commons Mathematics Library;
Development environment: The NetBeans IDE with Beans Binding Library for the implementation of the application GUI and JOGL2 usage.
